# start at 2006, pull the data, and loop the next 9 years (2022, the most recent complete season)
url = "https://www.pro-football-reference.com/years/2006/passing.htm"
dfs = []

for i in range(2006, 2023):
    # load page and pulls table with stats
    re = requests.get(url)
    root = BeautifulSoup(re.content)
    t = root.find("table")

    # convert to dataframe and add column indicating year
    df = pd.read_html(str(t))[0]
    df["year"] = [i for k in range(0, df["GS"].count())]

    dfs.append(df)
    url = url.replace(str(i), str(i+1))
In [ ]:
qb = []

# loop through the entire table and keep stats im interested in
for i in range(0, len(dfs)):
    df = dfs[i]
    # remove repeated column headers
    df = df[~df["Rk"].str.contains("Rk")]

    # filter for qb
    df = df[df["Pos"]=="QB"]

    # type conversion
    df["Rk"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Rk"])
    df["TD"] = pd.to_numeric(df["TD"])
    df["Int"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Int"])
    df["Yds"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Yds"])
    df["Player"] = df["Player"].astype('string')
    df["QBrec"] = df["QBrec"].astype('string')
    df["QBR"] = df["QBR"].astype(float)
    df["ANY/A"] = df["ANY/A"].astype(float)

    # remove null values
    df = df[~df["QBrec"].str.contains("NaN")]
    df = df[~df["QBrec"].str.contains("nan")]

    # filter for top 32 qbs (aka QB1s)
    df = df[df["Rk"] < 33]

    # filter for starters (more than half the season)
    df["GS"] = pd.to_numeric(df["GS"])
    df = df[df["GS"] > 7]
    qb.append(df)


# combine tables from each year
table = qb[0]
for i in range(1, len(qb)):
    table = table.append(qb[i])

table = table[["Player", "QBrec", "Cmp%", "TD", "Int", "ANY/A", "QBR", "Sk", "year"]]

# data cleansing / calculations
names = []
comp_r = []
winrate = []
sks_g = []
tds_g = []
ints_g = []
td_int = []

for x in table.itertuples():

  # convert record into winrate
  record = x[2].split("-")
  games = int(record[0]) + int(record[1])+int(record[2])
  winrate.append(int(record[0])/games)

  # remove Pro Bowl and All-Pro indicators
  names.append(x[1].replace("*", "").replace("+", "").strip())

  # convert completion % to actual rate (75% to .75)
  comp_r.append(float(x[3])/100)

  # calc stats to per game to account for missing some games
  sks_g.append(int(x[8])/games)
  td_int.append(int(x[4])/int(x[5]))

  tds_g.append(int(x[4])/games)
  ints_g.append(int(x[5])/games)

table["win_rate"] = winrate
table["Player"] = names
table["Sk"] = sks_g
table["TD"] = tds_g
table["Int"] = ints_g
table["td_int"] = td_int
table["Cmp%"] = comp_r

for p in lst:
  plt.subplots(figsize = (12, 8))

  col = p[0]
  pos = p[1]
  for y in table["year"].unique():
    year = table[(table==y).any(axis=1)]
      # temp remove brady and mahomes to add labels later
    year = year[~year["Player"].str.contains("Brady")]
    year = year[~year["Player"].str.contains("Mahomes")]

    plt.scatter(marker = "x", x = year["win_rate"], y = year[col], label=str(i))
    i+=1

  for x in table.itertuples():
    name = x[1]
    completion_rate = x[2]
    win_rate = x[8]
    if(name == "Patrick Mahomes"):
      plt.scatter(marker="o", x = x[8], y = x[pos])
      plt.annotate(str(x[10])+ " " + x[1], (x[8], x[pos]))
    if(name == "Tom Brady"):
      plt.scatter(marker="o", x = x[8], y = x[pos])
      plt.annotate(str(x[10])+ " " + x[1], (x[8], x[pos]))

  win_rate = np.array(table["win_rate"]).reshape(-1, 1)
  comp_rate = np.array(table[col]).reshape(-1, 1)

  reg = LinearRegression().fit(win_rate, comp_rate)
  plt.plot(win_rate, reg.intercept_ + reg.coef_ * win_rate, '-')


  x = "win rate"
  y = p[0]
  plt.xlabel(x)
  plt.ylabel(y)
  plt.title(y + " vs " + x)
  plt.show()

stat = 'completion_rate'

# filter for Tom Brady and Patrick Mahomes
players = ['Tom Brady', 'Patrick Mahomes']
filtered_data = table[table['Player'].isin(players)]

# boxplot for each year
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.boxplot(x='year', y=stat, data=table)

# not actually the median as each player only has one value for each year
yearly = filtered_data.groupby(['year', 'Player'])[stat].median().reset_index()
for _, row in yearly.iterrows():
    player = row['Player']
    year = row['year']
    completion_rate = row[stat]
    plt.text(year - 2006 + players.index(player) * 0.2 - 0.1, completion_rate, player, ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel(stat)
plt.title('Boxplot of ' + stat + ' by Year with Player Labels')
plt.show()

stats_to_plot = ['completion_rate', 'td_rate', 'int_rate', 'ANY/A', 'QBR', 'sack_rate', 'win_rate', 'td_int']

# filter for years 2018-2022 for both players
common_data = selected_rows[(selected_rows['year'].isin(range(2018, 2023))) & (selected_rows['Player'].isin(['Tom Brady', 'Patrick Mahomes']))]

# for loop to create chart per stat
for stat in stats_to_plot:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    for player in ['Tom Brady', 'Patrick Mahomes']:
        player_data = common_data[common_data['Player'] == player]
        plt.plot(player_data['year'], player_data[stat], marker='o', label=player)

    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel(stat)
    plt.title(f'{stat} Comparison for Tom Brady and Patrick Mahomes (2018-2022)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.xticks(player_data['year'])
    plt.tight_layout()

    plt.show()

stats_to_compare = ['completion_rate', 'td_rate', 'int_rate', 'ANY/A', 'QBR', 'sack_rate', 'td_int']

# scatterplots with lin_reg line and correlation coefficient label for each statistic vs. 'win_rate'
for stat in stats_to_compare:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    plt.scatter(table[stat], table['win_rate'], alpha=0.7)

    # calc lin_reg line
    m, b = np.polyfit(table[stat], table['win_rate'], 1)
    plt.plot(table[stat], m * table[stat] + b, color='red')

    plt.xlabel(stat)
    plt.ylabel('win_rate')
    plt.title(f'Scatterplot: {stat} vs win_rate')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()

    # Annotate the correlation coefficient value on the plot
    plt.annotate(f'Correlation: {np.corrcoef(table[stat], table["win_rate"])[0,1]:.2f}',
                 xy=(0.5, 0.9), xycoords='axes fraction',
                 ha='center', fontsize=8, color='blue')

    plt.show()

qbr_counts = {}

# loop through each year
for year in table['year'].unique():
    # filter data for the specific year
    year_data = table[table['year'] == year]

    # top 5 QBR each year
    top5_players = year_data.nlargest(5, 'QBR')['Player'].tolist()

    # if new player, added with count 1
    # if in list, increment count
    for player in top5_players:
        if player in qbr_counts:
            qbr_counts[player] += 1
        else:
            qbr_counts[player] = 1

for player, count in qbr_counts.items():
    print(player + ", Top 5 QBR: "+ str(count))
